Development assistance
----------------------
This project is developed with the assistance of Anthropic's Claude Code.
Every AI-assisted change is human-reviewed before landing. See
README.md "Disclaimers" for the full statement.

Acknowledgements
----------------
Dilithion stands on the shoulders of a number of open-source projects.
We gratefully acknowledge the work of:

  * Bitcoin Core developers
    https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin
    Ported patterns for AddrMan, peer scoring, compact blocks,
    headers sync, and consensus engineering.

  * pqcrystals/dilithium (NIST FIPS 204 reference implementation)
    https://github.com/pqcrystals/dilithium
    Post-quantum digital signatures.

  * tevador/RandomX
    https://github.com/tevador/RandomX
    CPU-friendly, ASIC-resistant proof-of-work.

  * Chia Network / chiavdf
    https://github.com/Chia-Network/chiavdf
    Verifiable delay function implementation.

  * OpenZeppelin Contracts (bridge / Base L2)
    https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts
    Audited primitives for the wrapped-token ERC-20s.

  * NIST SP 800-208, FIPS 202 (SHA-3 / Keccak), FIPS 204 (Dilithium)
    Standards the implementation is measured against.

  * Python, CMake, Boost, GMP, LevelDB, libsecp256k1 — foundational
    libraries that Dilithion depends on.
